premise_source_doc_sentence: Dane William DeHaan  (  -LSB- dəˈhɑːn -RSB- ; born February 6 , 1986  )  is an American actor .

He is known for playing Jesse on the HBO series In Treatment , and for his roles in the films Chronicle  (  2012  )  , The Place Beyond the Pines  (  2013  )  , Kill Your Darlings  (  2013  )  , The Amazing Spider-Man 2  (  2014  )  , Life  (  2015  )  and A Cure for Wellness  (  2016  )  .
In 2013 , Dubin directed the documentary film Hit The Lights-The Making Of Metallica Through The Never about the making of Metallica Through The Never starring Metallica and actor Dane DeHaan .
The film stars the voices of Elle Fanning , Dane DeHaan , Maddie Ziegler and Carly Rae Jepsen .

The film stars Andrew Garfield as Peter Parker / Spider-Man , Emma Stone as Gwen Stacy , Dane DeHaan as Green Goblin / Harry Osborn , Campbell Scott and Embeth Davidtz as Peter 's parents , and Sally Field as Aunt May , with the addition of a new cast including Paul Giamatti as Rhino / Aleksei Sytsevich and Jamie Foxx as Electro / Max Dillon .
